# No emojis — use Lucide icons

The user dislikes emojis. Never use emoji characters in UI text, JSX, labels,
placeholders, headings, or code. Always use [Lucide](https://lucide.dev) icons
(`lucide-react`) instead.

```tsx
// BAD — emoji in the UI
<span>🎧 Nice listening!</span>
<span>{voice === "female" ? "👩 Mei" : "👨 Tom"}</span>

// GOOD — Lucide icon
import { Headphones, UserRound } from "lucide-react";

<span className="flex items-center gap-1">
  <Headphones className="size-4" /> Nice listening!
</span>
<span className="flex items-center gap-1">
  <UserRound className="size-3.5 text-primary" /> Mei
</span>
```

- Differentiate items with icon color (e.g. `text-primary`, `text-emerald-500`)
  rather than different emoji.
- This also applies to console output, commit messages, and docs unless the
  user explicitly asks for emojis.
